The paper deals with the computation complexity of multi-head 2-way automata, which is a topic related to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The paper also discusses the complexity classes such as L, NL, P, NP, PSPACE, which are fundamental topics in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper uses mathematical logic and proof techniques to establish the characterizations of these complexity classes, which is related to the sub-category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also deals with the use of auxiliary memory and restricted guesses, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT), respectively.
